# Track vendored Python wheels via git-lfs going forward.
#
# Wheels are needed by sandbox-images/openclaw/Dockerfile.base for a
# hermetic (no-PyPI) sandbox build. Historically they were stored as
# regular git blobs and bloated the repo to ~320 MB.
#
# Adoption strategy:
#   * Existing wheels stay as regular blobs (no history rewrite — that
#     would force every contributor to re-clone).
#   * Wheels added or replaced after this commit go to LFS instead.
#   * Over time the working-tree size shrinks naturally as old wheels
#     get rotated out.
#
# Users who just want to read code can skip the wheel download entirely
# with a partial clone — see README.md "Cloning the repository".
vendor/sandbox-wheels/*.whl filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
